         <entry n="1">
            <form type="lemma">
               <orth>poltergeist</orth>
               <pron notation="ipa">/ˈpɒltəɡʌɪst/</pron>
            </form>
            <gramGrp>
               <pos>noun</pos>
               <subc>countable</subc>
            </gramGrp>
            <sense>
               <def>A ghost or other supernatural being supposedly responsible for physical disturbances such as making loud noises and throwing objects about.</def>
               <cit type="example">
                  <quote>Psychic investigators supposed Gef was a poltergeist or perhaps a ghost.</quote>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym>Mid 19th century from German Poltergeist, from poltern ‘create a disturbance’ + Geist ‘ghost’.</etym>     
         </entry>
         <entry n="2">
